\title{Small-step operation semantics}

\p{A small-step semantics for a language ${T} of syntactic terms comprises two components:

\ul{
\li{a set of \em{execution states} #{S}}
\li{a \em{transition relation} #{s \rightarrow s'} on #{S} that relates each state
#{s} to each state #{s'} that may be reached by performaing a single execution step}}}
